Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Skin peptide tyrosine-tyrosine (natural AMPs; Skin peptide YY; skin-PYY, SPYY, Neuropeptide; UCLL1; frog, amphibians, animals; XXA)
Sequence Information.Source: skin, the South American arboreal frogPhyllomedusa bicolor

Literature Information.Literature: Antifungal activity.  Also, active against A. caviae (MIC 60 ug/ml), E. coli (15 ug/ml), E. faecalis (20 ug/ml), N. brasiliensis (MIC 30 ug/ml), C. neoJbrmans, C. albicans (MIC 25 ug/ml), M. canis (10 ug/ml), T. rubrum, A. simii (15 ug/ml), A. fumigatus (MIC 100 ug/ml). No hemolysis at 100 ug/ml.  (Vouldoukis et aL., 1996). Updated 5/2020; 7/2020
Literature Information.Author: Mor A., Chartrel N., Vaudry H., Nicolas P.1994
